rComments: J'ai bien aimé ce cours et le choix de lectures. Je cite souvent celui qui portait sur le translanguaging dans mes autres travaux. Je prendrai un autre cours avec Joël si j'ai l'option.

rComments: Cool person, great prof. You learn a lot.
Juste un vraiment bon gars. Sa matière est super intéressante et il la rend avec passion.
Lun des meilleurs profs. Il se démarque par son engouement, sa passion contagieuse, mais aussi pour sa structure. Le genre de profs qui inspirent !

Young dynamic prof. Incredibly knowledgeable, and very approachable. I also liked him because he actually cares about his students. A lot of people here seem to say that his courses are not hard, and its true. But I like to think that by taking a class with Joel, you youll just learn a lot and wont waste your money.

Best class I've had in years! Now at the University of Regina, teaching french and french ed classes. I left everyday with many concrete ideas, he's never boring, I actually feel like I learn something new every class. Would definitely recommend, he's always very helpful and willing to work with you.

rComments: Joel is one of these good people. Very smart, yet very open and accessible. His course wont be easy, but youre going to learn a lot. He also has this optimistic (yet quite critical) view of education thatll make you understand why its important to develop skills to be a good teacher. Highly recommended.

Joel was actually my prof at the University of Regina, I had him for core French education and grammar education. Loved him in both classes. He's knowledgeable, accessible, and knows how to concretely relate theory and practice. It definitely won't be the easiest class you take, but he's a fair grader and provides a lot of relevant feedback.

Completely agree with the other comments. Joel is an approachable prof, one who will make you think about what it means to teach French in a minority setting. He's not always an easy greater, but you'll learn a lot. And his passion for grammar is just awesome!
This guy will not only make you like grammar, he'll make you want to teach it well!!!!!  Not an easy course. But a relevant one.
Excellent prof. Très brillant. Dynamique et disponible. Travaux intéressants. La BS dans les devoirs ne passera pas...

Joel gave the best online course I've taken! He met with us once a week to discuss the readings and the homework. He was always available to answer questions by email (ubber quick!), by phone or in person. He taught a mandatory intro to research course and managed to make it interesting!
